The paper deals with the analysis of a stochastic optimization algorithm for solving the Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP), which is a classic problem in computer science. The algorithm is based on a combination of Cross-Entropy and Max-Min Ant System, and the analysis involves the study of the impact of sample size on the runtime for different types of TSP instances. This type of research is typically found in the sub-fields of optimization (cs.NE), algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
